This paper deals with point cloud registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The use of structured light and flash LiDAR sensors, stereo reconstruction, and the iterative closest point algorithm all suggest that this paper is likely to be in the computer vision (cs.CV) or robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of a hidden Markov random field model and the EM algorithm suggest that this paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the problem of outlier rejection is a common issue in computer graphics (cs.GR), which further supports the inclusion of this paper in the above sub-categories.
